<F P=100> WEST AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Ghana </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To Seek Compensation From Togo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AB1001134794 Accra Ghana Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in English 1300 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> AB1001134794 </F>
<F P=104>  Accra Ghana Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The minister of foreign affairs, Dr. Obed Asamoah, 
has said that the Government of Ghana would take steps to ensure 
that the Togolese Government pays compensation to the families 
of the Ghanaians killed during last week's political 
disturbances in Lome. Speaking to the GBC [Ghana Broadcasting 
Corporation] in Accra, Dr. Asamoah said the government will 
insist that Togo pay reparations for damages caused to Ghana. 

</TEXT>

